        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>    

    <mj-section>
      <mj-column>
        <mj-image alt="Greenery, 2023." src="https://github.com/mjcampagna/mjml/blob/main/newsletters/202306/20230428-191203-mc-0964.jpg?raw=true" />
        <mj-text css-class="article">
          <p>Hi [Name,fallback=Friend],</p>
          <p>It's a busy month at The Turning Gate! We've just rolled out the 5.3.0 update, which is HUGE for Kookaburra. Plus, we have some notices regarding Font Awesome and Google Analytics; see below.</p>
          <p>Meanwhile, my yard is full of adorable rabbits, and summer -- only just begun! -- is already moving too quickly for my liking. Can someone just turn the speed down to 0.5x, like on a podcast?</p>
        </mj-text>        
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section>
      <mj-column>
        <mj-image alt="" src="https://github.com/mjcampagna/mjml/blob/main/newsletters/202306/essay-presentation-composer.jpg?raw=true" />

        <mj-text css-class="article">
          <h2>Essay anywhere in Backlight 5.3.0 + Kookaburra</h2>
          <p>Version 5.3.0 brings essay features and significant essay improvements to Kookaburra!</p>

          <p>From my very first line of code for Kookaburra, I have been laying foundation, working toward this release, and these new essay features. I am extremely pleased they are finally made manifest, no longer dwelling as mere ideas in my mind.</p>

          <p>&#8220;Essay anywhere!&#8221; means that you can now blend images and text anywhere in Kookaburra, on any page, in any album or set. You can include images from any published album, and mix images from multiple albums into a single slideshow. Album and essay presentations draw from the same configuration options in the page template, making them visually and functionally indistinguishable. And existing Pangolin essays are easy to migrate; just switch them to a Kookaburra template!</p>

          <p>There&#8217;s more in this release, including multi-language support for Kookaburra. For complete details, visit our blog post, <cite><a href="https://blog.theturninggate.net/2023/06/23/backlight-5-3-0-essay-anywhere-in-kookaburra/">Backlight 5.3.0: Essay Anywhere in Kookaburra!</a></cite></p>
        </mj-text>        
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section>
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text css-class="article">
          <h2>Regarding Font Awesome Pro and missing icons</h2>
          <p>Our Font Awesome Pro subscription has expired. In April, I wrote about <a href="https://discourse.theturninggate.net/t/upcoming-changes-to-font-awesome/2814">Upcoming Changes to Font Awesome</a> in Backlight. If you have any questions or require background, please read that post. I expect users will fall into one of the following buckets:</p>
          <p>&bull; If you are running the latest Backlight 5, or an older version of Backlight (3 or below), then you should not be impacted by our subscription expiring.</p>
          <p>&bull; If you are running an prior version of Backlight 5,you may find missing icons on your site. Upgrading to the latest version should resolve this.</p>
          <p>&bull; If you are running Backlight 4, you may find that icons are missing on your site. If this is the case, you have a few potential solutions.</p>

          <p><strong>The easiest solution, upgrade to Backlight 5</strong>.</p>
          <p>However, we are not in the business of forcing upgrades. Therefore, if you cannot upgrade to Backlight 5 at this time, or you find it unpalatable to do so in this situation, I have two more potential solutions for you:</p>

          <p>1. Follow <a href="https://ttg-tips-and-tricks.barbeephoto.com/font-awesome-5-free-unicode-fix/">Rod Barbee's guide, "Font Awesome 5 Free Unicode Fix"</a> to update the icons yourself, OR ...</p>
          <p>2. Contact me directly, and I will personally intervene to make any necessary repairs. To do so, I will require access to your Backlight admin, and FTP login credentials.</p>
          <p>Should you have any further concerns or questions, you may reply to this newsletter.</p>
        </mj-text>        
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section>
      <mj-column>
        <mj-image alt="" src="" />
        <mj-text css-class="article">
          <h2>Google Analytics 3 End-of-life</h2>
          <p>Sayth Google:</p>
          <p>"On July 1, 2023, standard Universal Analytics properties will no longer process data. You'll be able to see your Universal Analytics reports for a period of time after July 1, 2023. However, new data will only flow into Google Analytics 4 properties."</p>
          <p>Do remember that <a href="https://blog.theturninggate.net/2022/10/09/update-backlight-5-0-3/">we introduced support for the newer Google Analytics 4 into the Backlight 5.0.3 update</a>. If you haven't already made the switch, now is the time! See that blog post for details.</p>
          <p>I will very likely be removing Google Analytics 3 code from Backlight 5 in whatever update lands first after July 1, since by then it will be entirely useless.</p>
        </mj-text>        
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section>
